-It's a prime number.
-Could be a prime number.

00:14:49.087 --> 00:14:51.056
It's going to be hard to test
that without writing a script.

00:14:51.089 --> 00:14:52.491 size:63% position:69%
Just divide, divide,
divide, divide.

00:14:52.524 --> 00:14:53.992
[man]
Let's do a little division.

00:14:54.025 --> 00:14:55.594
[Michael]
<i> Just like the Arecibo message,</i>

00:14:55.627 --> 00:14:58.096
<i> our meaningless image contains</i>

00:14:58.129 --> 00:15:02.234
<i> 1,679 total tones.</i>

00:15:02.267 --> 00:15:06.038
<i> The number 1,679 can only be
 divided into two prime numbers:</i>

00:15:06.071 --> 00:15:07.539
<i> 23 and 73.</i>

00:15:07.572 --> 00:15:09.975
<i> When you arrange
 the ones and zeros</i>

00:15:10.008 --> 00:15:13.011
<i> from the message
 into a 23-by-73 grid,</i>

